The paper deals with algorithmic discrepancy problems, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of computational geometry and combinatorics (cs.CG). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and computational techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CC (computational complexity). The paper also mentions the use of information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) in some of the techniques used.
